ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think="The dev_tools_cubit_test.dart doesn't use `expectLater` with streams.
It just calls methods and checks the state directly with `expect(cubit.state, ..
.)`.\n\nFor MatchListCubit, since we're testing asynchronous stream emissions, I
should use a different pattern. The simplest is:\n\n```dart\nfinal states = <Mat
chListState>[];\nfinal subscription = cubit.stream.listen(states.add);\n\nawait 
cubit.fetchMatches();\n\nawait Future.delayed(Duration.zero); // allow microtask
s to complete\n\nexpect(states, [\n  const MatchListLoadInProgress(),\n  isA<Mat
chListLoadSuccess>()...\n]);\n\nsubscription.cancel();\n```\n\nOr I can use `exp
ectLater` correctly. The key insight is:\n- For Bloc, you call `add()` first, th
en `await expectLater()` because events are processed asynchronously\n- For Cubi
t with async methods that emit synchronously, you need to set up the listener fi
rst, then trigger the method\n\nWait, but if I set up `expectLater` first and th
en call `fetchMatches`, it should work because `expectLater` starts listening im
mediately. Let me test this...\n\nActually, looking at my code:\n```dart\nawait 
expectLater(cubit.stream, emitsInOrder(expectedStates));\nawait cubit.fetchMatch
es();\n```\n\nThe problem is `await expectLater(...)` BEFORE `fetchMatches()`. `
expectLater` returns a Future that completes when the matcher is satisfied. Sinc
e no events have been emitted yet, it will wait forever.\n\nThe correct order sh
ould be:\n```dart\nfinal expectation = expectLater(cubit.stream, emitsInOrder(ex
pectedStates));\nawait cubit.fetchMatches();\nawait expectation;\n```\n\nOr, sin
ce `fetchMatches()` emits synchronously:\n```dart\ncubit.fetchMatches(); // don'
t await, or do await - but set up expectLater first\nawait expectLater(cubit.str
eam, emitsInOrder(expectedStates));\n```\n\nWait no, if `fetchMatches` emits syn
chronously and I call it before `expectLater`, the events are missed.\n\nLet me 
think about this more carefully:\n1. `cubit.fetchMatches()` is an async method\n
2. Inside `fetchMatches()`, it does `emit(const MatchListLoadInProgress())` whic
h is synchronous\n3. Then it awaits the repository call\n4. Then it emits the su
ccess state\n\nSo when I call `await cubit.fetchMatches()`:\n- Step 1: `emit(Loa
dInProgress)` happens synchronously before the first `await`\n- Step 2: The meth
od pauses at `await repository.getMatches(...)`\n- During this pause, the stream
listener can process the event\n\nBut `expectLater` needs to be set up BEFORE `e
mit(LoadInProgress)` is called.\n\nSo the correct pattern is:\n```dart\nfinal ex
pectation = expectLater(cubit.stream, emitsInOrder(expectedStates));\nawait cubi
t.fetchMatches();\nawait expectation;\n```\n\nOr, since `fetchMatches` starts wi
th a synchronous emit:\n```dart\n// DON'T await fetchMatches yet\nfinal future =
cubit.fetchMatches();\n// Now set up expectLater - but LoadInProgress might have
already been emitted!\nawait expectLater(cubit.stream, emitsInOrder(expectedStat
es));\n```\n\nNo, that won't work either because `future = cubit.fetchMatches()`
starts executing immediately, and `emit(LoadInProgress)` happens before the `awa
it` inside `fetchMatches`.\n\nActually, in Dart, when you call an async function
, the body starts executing synchronously until the first `await`. So:\n```dart\
nfinal future = cubit.fetchMatches();\n// At this point, emit(LoadInProgress) ha
s ALREADY happened\n```\n\nSo if I want to catch `LoadInProgress`, I MUST have t
he listener set up BEFORE calling `fetchMatches`.\n\nThe correct pattern is:\n``
`dart\nfinal expectation = expectLater(cubit.stream, emitsInOrder(expectedStates
));\nawait cubit.fetchMatches();\nawait expectation;\n```\n\nWait, but in my cod
e I had:\n```dart\nawait expectLater(cubit.stream, emitsInOrder(expectedStates))
;\nawait cubit.fetchMatches();\n```\n\nThe issue is that `await expectLater(...)
` waits for the matcher to complete. But the matcher won't complete until all ex
pected events are emitted. Since `fetchMatches` hasn't been called, no events ar
e emitted, so it waits forever.\n\nSo the fix is to NOT await `expectLater` unti
l after `fetchMatches`:\n\n```dart\nfinal expectation = expectLater(cubit.stream
, emitsInOrder(expectedStates));\nawait cubit.fetchMatches();\nawait expectation
;\n```\n\nLet me update the test.",
    encrypted=None
)
